\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Your address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 'Sylvan', Hoe Lane, Abridge, Romford, Essex.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Your marital status?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I'm a widow, aren't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 The year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 1891.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I was born in Leyton, London. Essex.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Twenty-four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What road was that in Leyton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Capworth Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Capworth Street, Leyton. And you lived there for 24 years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Then I lived in Vicarage Road, Leyton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was that when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How long did you stay in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Let's see ... 'till 1918, when the War finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I'd one ... my own brother, and two half-brothers and one half-sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Can you tell me how old they were and what order they came in? were you the eldest or the youngest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 The youngest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Of all the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Of all the children. Well, let's see. I know the eldest boy was 14 when I was born and I suppose his sister must have been about 15.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 She was older than he was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 And the other half-brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 He was 10, I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 And your own brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, he was 3 years older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was it your mother who'd married before or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 My father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 This was his second marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 He was a widower.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 He was 40.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, as far as I know he lived in Forest Gate. He'd lived there for some
 years. His father was the youngest son of seven sons, and he was the head auditor of the Great Eastern Railway Company in the goods department.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Who? Your grandfather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What was your father's occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, my father was ... we
ll, he started as a head clerk in a firm and then he became the secretary and one of the directors, of a builders merchants, and he was there for forty years in this firm and he never had a holiday, only a day occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 He never had a week's holiday, or two weeks' holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, until he became ill and that was the end of ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he only ever work for that one firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, he started as a clerk in the railway, but he quarreled with his father and left, and then he had this job with this
 firm, and he moved there when he was about 20 and he was 60 when he left ... when he became ill and left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he also do any casual or part-time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, he collected rents for the firm, the property they had, and he also used to do the book
s for a friend. This man, he was a glass bender but he couldn't read or write and he used to work for this firm, which the name was Dixon Head, and one day he thought he would start on his own. He got a little coster truck and he went round getting jobs .
.
. just small jobs, bending glass for ... well, just showcases and things like that. Well, he was very short of money and sometimes at the end of the week he had no money for himself, it had all gone in the business. Well, after that period he got on much 
b
etter and my father said to him, he said, 'Look here,' he said, 'what are you doing with your money?' He said, 'You'll have to have a banking account'. So he said, 'well, 'he said, 'I'm keeping it under the stairs,' so he said, 'well, that won't do'. So h
e
 said, 'but I can't write my own name'. So he said, 'well, I'll write your name and you must copy it and copy it 'till you can do it yourself'. And he took this man to the bank and introduced him and explained things, and this man eventually became quite 
a wealthy man and he used to ... glass bending became very popular. He had most of the work there was about.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your father help him to sort out his money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, he did his books for him. And of course, as some ... he used to pay him ... he use
d to go in the evening time twice a week, I can still remember, on Tuesdays and Wednesday evenings he used to go to this ... his name was Hudson, in fact I believe the remains of the firm is still going. And he used to do his books for him, which he used 
to pay him a small ... 10 shillings, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Can you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no, never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 She was 32.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 She lived in south London, I believe it was Walworth as far as I know. I know it was round that locality somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Had she any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, I believe she used to work in sewing, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 At home, do you know, or in a firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
No, she went out to a firm. I've heard her speak of a firm Hitchcock Williams which were very good people in London, they had a big warehouse and there was a very large shop round St. Paul's Churchyard. Whether they're going now I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did she have any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 The period I'm going to talk about now is when you were at home until the time you left school. How many rooms were there in your house?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, there was the 3 bedrooms and then there was what we called in those days, parlour, kitchen and scullery. And all these ... the kitchen and the scullery had a proper cooking range in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 The kitchen and the scullery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 There was 2 separate rooms and the scullery had a proper range in it, and so did the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did anyone else live in the house besides you and your brothers and sister?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No grandparents or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No. Sometimes Grandma came to stay with us, my mother's mother, but that wasn't permanent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Sometimes, not always. Sometimes the washing was sent out, or sometimes the washing was done at home, we had someone come in to help with the housework. But that wasn't a regular thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you ever have anyone living-in to help with the housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no, there wasn't room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 If somebody did come in to help with the housework did they just do the housework or did they help look after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no, just did the housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your mother or your father make or mend the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, my mother used to make some of my clothes when I was a little girl, but my father was very ... he was very handy with
 his hands, he could do practically anything, but he used to make us toys and things like that, but he never made any clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he mend any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your mother mend clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, of course, she did mend them, and stocking and soc
ks in those days used to be woolen and they used to wear out and that was all done at home of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were your clothes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, most of my ... I never remember having anything secondhand. All my clothes were new when I had them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you know where they were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, from the local shops. My mother used to buy material and make them for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 When did you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, we always had Sunday clothes in those days. In fact, I think Sunday was the hig
hlight in those days. I can remember I used to love being dressed up and go to Sunday School in the afternoon, and putting two fingers down one finger in the glove, you know what I mean. And that was a great thing for me to go ... be dressed up and go to 
Sunday School. And everybody, I think, however poor they were, they had that little dress or suit put to one side to put on for special occasions. Then you took that for everyday, and there was another new bought one ... a new one bought.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you have new ones at any special time of the year or just when it was necessary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I think Easter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7351471\charrsid9898441  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 time was a great time for having something new. And of course, Christmas, you'd very often have a new party dress or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What about shoes? Did your father or mother make or mend your shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were your shoes new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7351471\charrsid9898441  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, new, yes. I was one of the lucky ones, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 When did you have new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, when I grew out of the others or wore them out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house? Did he ever do any cleaning or cooking or washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, my father used to always do the vegetables on Sunday mornings. He was really quite a practical man, he could do an
ything. But of course, he didn't do it because, you see, he didn't get home 'till 2 o'clock on a Saturday afternoon and then we had to have a meal, or something, and ... Well, there wasn't much else to do. If he did anything, we'd sit round the table and 
he would make us toys and we would watch him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So he could do things in the house, but he just didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, he could, yes. Well, it really wasn't necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he ever lay the fires, or do any decorating or repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, no, he didn't do anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he dress or undress you, or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, he used to dress me in the morning, probably while my mother was getting the breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he read to you, or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, he would read. He was quite a good artist and he used to draw us wonderful pictures and stick them all over the wall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 And did he look after you when she was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, he was a good father, he was ... Oh, yes, very good father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you have any tasks that you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Not really. I used to do a good bit of shopping, but we didn't do much in the home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you have to clean the silver, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, when I got older we used to ... 'Course, in those days there wasn't stainless steel knives, we had a knife board and you had to clean them on the ... Because, you see, knives stained very quickly. You could clean
 a knife and use it once and it'd want polishing up again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you have to do this regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your brothers and sister have to do any jobs, since they were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Not that I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did the older ones have to look after you younger ones or help you with anything that you found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, you see, being such a lot of difference in our ages, they were grown up and ... Well, my sister, she went into domestic service - I don't know if it was a lady's maid, or what - and she went to Belgium.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 To Belgium?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
She went to Belgium, and I think she liked it out there and she liked the language. In fact ... I think it's a Catholic country, and she even took up the religion, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So she wasn't at home when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, you see, she was so much older than me, by the time I was 10, you see she was about 25.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your school days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, no, I never remember being ... laying 
the law 'you've got to go to bed'. Oh, no. I can remember my mother saying, 'look here, it's getting on for 9 o'clock, it's time you were in bed'
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, they generally came upstairs and saw us in bed. That was the regular thing, I think, to see your children properly in bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, no. No, I was ... You see, there was only my brother and I left at the latter part, and he had a room, I had a room,
 my parents had a room. You see, we had the 3 rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, we didn't have a bathroom. We used to have a large bath. In fact, I thought it was the nicest way of having a wash, we used to have this bath and a lovely fire, and the worst part about it was emptying them and filling them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Would this be in the scullery or the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 We used to have it in the kitchen. Oh, we used to make quite a to-do of that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, about once a week, I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, about once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, in the kitchen, as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, no, I don't remember ... We might 've gone in our parlour, as we called it, and had a spread, but not ... that was only on special occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your mother cook on a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 In the kitchen or scullery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, i
t all depends, of course. In the summertime we'd have a fire in the scullery then she would cook in there, but in the wintertime we'd have a fire in the kitchen and it was all nice and warm, and she would cook there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I think ... I suppose on Sundays about half past nine or ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What about during the week? Would you all have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no. We would ... of course, I'd go out to school about half past eight, well, I'd probably have my breakfast
, I suppose, about 8 o'clock. And my father, he used to go out when he liked, I think. He never went out of the house 'till about 10 o'clock, sometimes, some mornings, well that meant that we were at school while he was having his breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Can you remember what you usually ate and drank for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, we kept our own chickens and I think I had an egg nearly every morning for my breakfast, and we'd have egg and bacon, and the usual.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What about your midday meal, what would that be called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Oh, we called that our dinner, didn't we. Yes, that was our dinner. We always had a good dinner. My mother, I think she fed us on steak and potatoes and greens. Oh, yes, we always lived well. Of course, you could buy a very nice steak ... the bes
t steak was only 1/2d. a 1b. and you could buy quite a good steak for 8d. a 1b.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What was the evening meal called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 That was called supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Would the whole family be together for the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no. You see, Father wasn't at home. 
There'd be ... I can remember, like, my brother and my mother and myself. And then, of course, when my father came home, however late it was, even if he'd been to do his booking, he always had a proper meal. We had a fishmonger used to call round and we u
sed to buy fish from him and my mother used to fry it. And sometimes we didn't get to bed 'till 12 o'clock at night because Father didn't come in 'till about half past 10.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So would you wait up for him to have your supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I don't know, we used t
o wait for him. Yes, we waited for him, you see. That's why I remember Tuesdays and Wednesdays because I remember we didn't go to bed very early those two nights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Sometimes, not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
No, not in those days. I don't think people ... It wasn't 'till the First World War that I don't think people ever got down to that sort of thing because nobody was ever short of anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What about making pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I don't remember her making pickles. We used to buy pickles, but she didn't make them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What about making wine, or any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, she didn't make wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no, no, if there was any beer it was bought. It was bought as beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your mother or father grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, we grew quite a lot of vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 And you say that they kept chickens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you keep anything else, apart from chickens? Pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 My mother and father, and we were sometimes sent down to feed the chickens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you ever buy any vegetables or fruit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, of course, in the wintertime you have to because you haven't any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you ever have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I don't remember ever having anything like that? I don't think that there was so much of this dehydrated stuff in those d
ays. You see, it was genuine food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, I couldn't tell you. I suppose about 5 days a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you ever get some extra meat, such as rabbit, from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you ever remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 If there was something that you children particularly liked would she go without to let you have some more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, in our case it wasn't necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your father have more than the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, he didn't have more, but I think we always saved the best for Father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were you allowed to talk during meals, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked, or did you have to have a little of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I wasn't particularly keen on greens, but I was told that if I didn't eat me greens I wouldn't have a sweet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What was your parents' attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I never remember leaving any on the plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
If there was something that you wanted on the table, like the salt, could you ask for it to be passed or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I don't remember. It was always on the table and if you needed it you ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork, and sit, in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I always had to eat me food properly. And I always remember when I ... used to w
onder ... ask me mother and father which hand I put me knife and fork in because I could use both ways. You know, I used very often to have the fork in the right hand and the knife in the left hand and I did it so often that I was told off so many times t
hat in the end I used to say, 'now, which hand to I put my fork in?'
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No. No, we were not allowed to read at meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, we generally waited 'till we were all finished. I think it was just a habit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you all sit at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 And how was the meal served? Who served it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, my father always carve
d the meat, Mother usually served the vegetables. But of course, when Father wasn't there, Mother had to officiate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was your mother an easy person to talk to? Was she a motherly person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, she was a good mother and she looked after us well, but I don't know whether she was an easy person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Which of the two would you say was stricter with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 My father was very particular about ... if we went out we ... he 
wanted to know what time we were coming home, and if we didn't come in at that time he wanted to know where we'd been and what we'd been up to and if we didn't keep good time we were not going out any more. That sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 He was stricter in things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 He was a good father. As I say, he was a good father, my father was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I suppose he was. Yes, he was very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you get on well with both your parents or with one in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, I preferred my father. Yes, he was ... I think we had more in common together, and I can always remember my mother saying 'oh, she's like her father', so there must have been something between us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your mother show you affection? Was she an affectionate person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, she wasn't, no, no. She was a good mother. Oh, she was a good ... she looked after us well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 If you had any worries could you share them with her, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I suppose I could. I don't remember much. Of cour
se, when I went to school the latter part of the time her education wasn't up as much as mine. And then, with my father, he did things his way but it wasn't the way I would do them, you see, you can't ... The generations ... one generation can't help anot
her generation because they have different methods. When I hear the little children talking about the way they were learnt to spell, they've got it all different to the ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, from the way you learnt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, this is very true. Was your father an affectionate person, did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, he was. He was more affectionate, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 If you had any worries could you share them with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, and he'd take the matter up, too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I don't know, really. All I know is that we had to do as we were told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 They expected obedience?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes. Beyond that ... well, we played at games and we read and we did anything that we ... as long as we behaved ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did they bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I think we just naturally fell in with one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 If you were playing and another child hit you and you told your parents, would their attitude be that you should hit them back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, we were brought up not to fight. If there was anything, 'come home.' 'Get out of it'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What kind of people do you think they hoped you'd grow up to be? Did they feel that certain things in life were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I don't think so. They didn't seem to consider that, as long as ... you know, we behaved ourselves and didn't get into any trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were they ambitious for you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, t
hey didn't encourage swearing. I can remember when my brother went to the Board school they found the boys swore, and they he came home and swear because he thought it was the thing to do and my father says, 'well, you can swear, but not here'.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 When grownups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I just think we didn't attempt to join in, we didn't unless we were spoken to, it was part of our nature.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I think my father would be in a rage, he was that type of man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Would he punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Might give me a good talking to, but I don't think he'd do much else, and say 'well, if we have any more of it we'll have to see what can be done'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What about your mother? What would she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I don't know, I think she left things to Father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, not really, no. Of course, I ... I don't want to blow me own trumpet, but I've heard
 my parents say they didn't remember me much as a child, I was so quiet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So you didn't get into trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I don't remember getting into trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents, or did 
one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
I don't think so. Perhaps if I was going out to tea me mother would give me a little talking to before I went, because Father wouldn't be there, would he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I'd have some presents and then perhaps some children in to tea, but nothing extra.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I don't seem to remember anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you have Christmas at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did anybody else come to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, perhaps the eldest brother that ... you know, they were working away. They would come, come home to dinner Christmas time. But ...

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What would you all do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 We might just play cards, or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Your parents, as well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, we had a piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Who played the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, my eldest ... my half-sis
ter, she was quite a good pianist, and then my brother, the eldest boy, he played the ... he bought himself a banjo and played the banjo, so they used to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I was taught, yes. But, you see, my father's first wife was a very good pianist and that's where the musical section came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your mother play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I don't ever remember her playing, no. My father played very nicely by ear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, Ted, my eldest brother, he sang. He sang very nicely, he had a good baritone voice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, we used to, yes, with our banjo and the piano. You had to in those days because there wasn't anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 When would you do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, in the evening times, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your parents play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Not really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes. There was always plenty of literature.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I don't know. Mother never seemed to have much time to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, sometimes my father would read a tale to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he ever read to your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, she'd read herself if she wanted to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you remember a funeral in the family before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, my father died in 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Can you remember that funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I wonder if you could tell me a little bit about it, you know, what clothes people wore and what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, everybody wore black. You was disrespectful if you didn't wear black. It was quite the thing. And, of course, we had horses. And it was only ... he was buried in the churchyard, 
Leyton, but it wasn't far away, it was only about a mile from the house, if that. And, of course, we just went to the church and there was a service and of course, we went to the graveside, and then we came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was there tea or any refreshments for anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, we ... those that came to the funeral, there was just a tea, but it was all done in a very simple way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you ride in a carriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes. Oh, yes. There were, as I say, horses, and the horses wore a kind of - I don't know 
what they called them - a kind of decora ... plume things on their heads and they had lovely velvet drapes over the horses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 All black, yes. Yes, they were very, very nice. But of course, the motorcar's done away with all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, sometimes, yes. That was our only way of a change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Who generally took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, my mother, as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, we always went shopping with Mum, if it was only to carry the things home.(laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You said earlier that your father did take you out without your mother, can you remember anywhere in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, sometimes we'd go down to Southend. Of course, you could go to Southend 
for 2/6d. in those days, which I suppose was a lot of money, but it was the return journey. And that was the nearest seaside to London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You went with your brother, was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, sometimes I want on me own and sometimes my brother went. And I ca
n remember when I was quite a little girl - or I wasn't very old - there was the Indian Exhibition on at Earls Court and it was a great joke in the family. They said 'where is Walter?' 'Oh, I said', he's gone to Injun B exhibition', so it'll tell you how 
old I was (laughter)
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Who was Walter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 My own brother, yes. And that was a great joke, the Injun B exhibition, so it'll tell you how old I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You didn't go to that exhibition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no, I suppose I was only about 4.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So your father did used to take you out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Yes, well, my mother took my brother out to that because it was on a working day, you see. And mother always took ... when we were older she always took us to London. We went to St. Paul's Cathedral, the Tower of London, Mad
ame Tussaud's, Westminster Abbey. She always took us to places of interest. And I was very much surprised at school, there were several girls in the school, in the class, that had never been to London. And we were only 5 or 6 miles away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 But your parents did take you out to places like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you ever go on outings with both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, we went to the Zoo, and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You said earlier that your father never had a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, not a week's holiday, it was all bits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Not much. Not much because, you see, I can remember going to Dovercourt for a week's holiday, or something like that, with Mother. But, you see, circumstances ... when a man's always at work 
you can't leave him much, can you. In fact, people didn't go for holidays like they do now. I suppose is was after the ... like, 1914 War, after that that people began to go away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Can you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What did I
 do? I might go out and get a few errands for my mother. And then, of course, we'd have to help lay the table and get the meal ready. And then after that we would ... I don't know. Might go out looking at the shops, or perhaps there'd be something on down
 at the church and we'd go down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, of course, my people were not religious people. They didn't go to church, but the children had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you go to church in the mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Sometimes, yes, but I'd more of
ten go ... I had a girlfriend and I would go in the evening time. I think it was more to break the monotony of the day because it was definitely a day of ... well ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So it was partly to relieve the monotony?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes. It was such a quiet day. And, of course, Sunday was respected, well to a young person it was rather boring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were you able to play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 We just didn't play games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, it was a day of rest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did they ever attend Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 My mother might go sometimes, but my father didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You said that you went to Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were there any Sunday School outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, if there was my mother never let me go out on any outings lik
e that. I never went out with a Sunday School treat. But we always had a Sunday School party with a Christmas Tree and things like that, which was a great thing in my life, the Sunday School Christmas party. I was allowed to go to that, but I was never al
lowed on Sunday School treats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you know why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
No, I don't know why at all. Of course, in those days they had breaks, what they call a brake and horses and the children used to go in the brakes and they used to sing. I used very often to walk in
to the Lea Bridge Road just to see the brakes going by, the children going on their outing. I never wanted to go. Although I wasn't allowed to go it never grieved me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 But you just used to go and watch them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I used to watch them, yes, and I'd go 
down to the Sunday School and see them going off. But I think my mother was very strange like that, she never seemed to let me go out with a crowd. I don't know why. But talking of brakes I remember it was one of my treats of a Bank Holiday to walk down t
o the Lea Bridge Road and see the Harry and Harriet\rquote 
s they talked about with their ostrich feathers and their pearly kings sitting in the brakes, they all went out ... It was really very, very nice. And there was a man, name of Clark, he was a decorator and
 every year these men had what they called The Bean Feast in those days. And he used to have 2 brakes and all his workmen used to go on this ... on the brake. And he always used to play the horn as they were starting off, like, you know. They used to have
 a horn. And I can remember that very plainly. Blowing the horn, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were there any other social activities organised by the church that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 We'd a magic lantern show, and they used to run little plays for youngsters to go in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you go to these?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Yes. And I remember they used to run a kind of gymnastic class or something like that in the evening times. Oh, and they has the Girls' Friendly Society and the Band of Hope, which the church ran all those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you go to those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, in the evening time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
No, no. My eldest brother used to. He belonged to the choir, and then he left it, and I said to him 'why did you leave?' and he said, 'they stopped paying me' (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Not in my family, no. But in many families there was Grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes. He was a strong Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you know why he held those views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, he always said that trade was better when the Conservative government was in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he think that the working man had a square deal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, he didn't have a square deal, the working man. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your mother take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you remember your father or mother voting in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, of course, women didn't have the vote when my mother was ... But my father always voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was he a member of the Conservative Party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you remember him working for his party at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, no, he wasn't all that keen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 When they weren't doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, there really wasn't much time left, was there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What time did your father come home in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, he didn't come home 'till about 7 o'clock at night. You see, most people worked 'till 6 o'clock at night, I 
suppose it was 7 o'clock when he came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What would he do after he'd had his meal? He went out two evenings a week to do the books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, that's right, yes. 'Course, he never came home, he went straight to the job. But ... oh, I think he used 
to read the newspaper and he smoked a pipe, used to sit by the fire and smoke a pipe or read the paper or ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he attend any pubs or clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
On the quiet (laughter). Well, when he did bet he told me that once he took a year betting and he worked it out at the end of the year that he was about, with his losses and his gains, he was back where he started. You see, he was evidently a mathe
matician, wasn't he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So he worked these things out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Never, no. I don't remember her going ... I don't think women did in those days. And, of course, everything took much longer
; the washing day took all day long, it only takes about 2 or 3 hours today. And I can remember having the first gas stove, which was quicker, but the ordinary stove ... you know, you had to wait for the stuff to get hot and all that sort of thing. There 
wasn't much time for anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did she ever have neighbours, or anybody, popping in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Sometimes, but we were more ... we didn't encourage that sort of thing. We liked to keep friends, and we found that a lot of those people that've got that sort of habit, they generally ended up in being bad friends. That's right, isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How did you get on with your brothers and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, all right, they were very good to me. I think, perhaps, I was the pet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, of course, my own brother he was with me a lot. In fact, he died when he was 26 and ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, dear! How was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I can't understand it. You know, he was a tailor's cutter and I think they said he died of cancer o
n the lung, but I think it was the fluff from the material got on his lungs. And he said to me one day, 'I don't know what's the matter with me,' he said, 'It's hard work for me to walk along this road'. That was at Easter. Easter 1915. He died about 8 mo
n
ths after my father. And then he got worse and he couldn't breathe very well. He went to the doctor's and the doctor said he'd got bronchial catarrh. Well, a friend suggested he went to hospital, and he went to the hospital and they kept him in. and he wa
s in the hospital 3 weeks and he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was that his only job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, he was apprenticed to that. He was apprenticed to that trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So it could well be that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes. I think that it was the ... 'Cos in those days there was no electric fa
ns or anything to take away that sort of thing, like a lot of trades killed people years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was he married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So that was a very difficult time for your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 It was, yes. It was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, there was the children next door and there was my brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Mostly in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you ever play in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Sometimes, not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 And what about other people's homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, sometimes we went in with one another to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Oh, we used to ... 'Course, one of the great was mothers and fathers (laughter), that was always ... Oh, I don't know, we used to play round. I can remember playing what we called Statues
; and ... what was it they used to call? In and Out The Windows. Stand in a ring and all hold hands and hold them high up, and then one girl or boy whoever we were playing with, used to go in and out, in and out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I did get dirty and I got told off about it, but I was one of these people that just got dirty (laughter).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I can't imagine that now. Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no, no, no. If my parents thought that they were not decent people I was told to avoid them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you know what things would put them off other children? What did they mean by 'decent'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 If they felt they came from a dirty home or there was any bad living in the family. I very often was
n't told why, but I was not to play with so-and-so, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 When I got older I belonged to the Shaftesbury Society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I believe it's going today. This was a ... we used t
o look after the cripples. Yes, the Shaftesbury Society. There was Sir William Trelaw, he was once Lord Mayor of London and he had a kind of organisation, and then there was this Lord Shaftesbury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What did you actually do to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, we used 
to meet, like, once a week, we used to play games and we used to put pennies in the box and all the things like that, we used to collect and when there was a certain amount the organiser used to send the money to the head office, I suppose. And then, if w
e knew of anybody who wanted crutches, or anything like that, we used to try and buy them. Because, you see, it wasn't a welfare state in those days. And we used to have very nice parties and enjoy ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How did you spend your free time? Did you have any hobbies? Or did you keep any pets, or collect anything or do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
I used to have my little piece of gardening, but I used to do a lot of sewing, you know, when I was ... And I loved dolls and dressed dolls, and I was very fond of ne
edlework. I always had a piece of patchwork going, you know, sewing any old odd pieces together and making things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes. I can remember as a little girl my uncle, they lived in Wimbledon, and there was the W
andle where Lady Hamilton lived, you know, to do with Nelson. Well, I had a cousin, a boy, he was the same age as me and we used to have a jam jar and a net and we used to go down the Wandle to catch the fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Not a lot. I 
can remember going for a walk with a girlfriend once in the Forest, and I can remember getting told off because I didn't know anything about wicked things happening, but I came home safely. But we walked into Epping Forest, we had a very nice time and whe
n I got home I got told off for going in the Forest. I didn't know why. I was never told why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Things weren't explained to you, you were just told not to do things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Just that and you'd got to accept it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I did mind because I didn't know why and I never did anything that my parents would not approve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Could you ask why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, if I did they'd say 'well never mind why'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you ever go bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I never went. My brother used to go but I wasn't keen on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, no. I don't think we were sport people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you go to any theatres or concerts or music halls or cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I went to my first pantomime, I was 5 years old at the Borough Theatre, Stratfor
d, and I thought it was marvellous. It was beautiful. It was Cinderella and I've never seen anything so beautiful in all my life. I can see that lovely transformation scene now, with the fairy godmother and Cinderella.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 This was when you were 5?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you go much after that, as you got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 We used to go to the pantomime every Christmas. We'd go somewhere, but that was only a yearly treat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You didn't go to any music halls or theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Not 'till later in life, I wasn't al
lowed to. It wasn't considered decent for young women. Music hall was very low. A play, yes, that would be all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you go to any plays while you were a schoolgirl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, there was plenty, like, the local theatre would have a play on and we would go to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, I always had pocket money. I think I had three pence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What did you spend the money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I put two pence in the money box and the penny I used to buy some sweets with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, no. Didn't you ask that ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes. I meant this time. Did her relatives or anybody come in to give a hand?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, luckily I don't remember her being ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your parents see much of your relatives? You said your father's family ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, but you see, he fell out with his father and he never bothered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What about his brothers? Did you see much of your uncles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
No, no, we didn't ... My mother had one brother and one sister which they both lived in Wimbledon and I didn't see much of those. 'Course, travelling, it was quite a business, you know, going from one place to another. Very slow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, they didn't seem to have friends very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were people ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, they used to just come in and have a chat, but they didn't make a ..
. I don't think people did in those days. The children were friendly and used to come in to one another's houses for tea, and that, but I don't remember them ... you know, Mrs. So-and-so going round to Mrs. Somebody-else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Your parents didn't have a lot of people coming into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did they ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
No, no. They didn't. I think there was always ... everything seemed to take up your time, there wasn't time to, as far as I remember. You seemed to ... you spent your time cleaning out fireplaces and lighting fires. Everything took such a long time to do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Many people d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5856267\charrsid9898441 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 vide society into different social classes or groups - this is before 1918 - did you think of some people as belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Yes. I think the men in clerical positions thought they were superior to the house decorator and all that sort of thing. Yes, oh, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What were these different groups or classes called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, of course, I can
 remember there was a working man's club, but I don't think the white-collar worker, as you would call him, I don't remember them talking about them having any ... I don't know what you'd call it ... association, or ... I've never heard of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Would you have regarded people as working class, middle class and upper class? Or what phrase was used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Of course, those in the house where I lived was quite ... as you know there was no bathroom or anything like that, but most of the people round us had very good jobs, you see, we'll say. My neighbours next}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5856267\charrsid9898441  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
door, he was a teacher, and then there was a neighbour just round the corner, he was a ... he used to ... he was a reader for the Daily Telegraph. And these people, you know, they had really quite ... but that's the only type of house they lived in.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 All of you had similar sort of accommodation in your area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What class or group would you say you belonged to, yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I suppose we were not rich and we were not poor. I suppose you'd call us the middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 And these other people round you, like the reader and the teacher, would you say they were a similar sort of class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, very nice people, they were. They were really very nice people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What sort of people belonged to the other classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, of course, there was the painter and bricklayer, and those people in the building trade, there was those. But of course, where we lived, from that there'd only be, like, the aristocracy in 
the neighbourhood which was a very small percentage. Like on the Barklay's estate there was the Barklay}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5856267\charrsid9898441 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
s ... I don't know. Of course, in those days there was rich people, but I don't know whether they were what you'd call aristocracy, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Who were rich people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, there were some people called ... their name was Simons and they ... I believe they were butchers, but they were butchers in a very big ... They didn't have butchers shops, I think they were market people and that sort of ... yo
u know, in the meat market. But I know there's a road in Leyton now called Simons Road. Well, they were very well off and they used to ... it wasn't in my time, my half-brother, and that, they used to give the children in the ... it was a village then, a 
party every year. They always had a Christmas party. All the children went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Even when you were a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, when I grew up it had stopped, they were gradually going, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Who were the most important people in your village when ... that you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, of course, from what I can remember ... I don't seem to remember much about these ... as I say, these rich people. They seemed to be fading out, their estates were sold. But I remember when I used to go to Church on a Sunday morning
 all the local shopkeepers in the high road, all the men - the shopkeepers - they all wore their top hats and frock coats and went to church in them. And I can remember them coming out of church and standing outside and they were all standing there having
 a chat. But they really did look gentlemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No. But I instinctively picked people out myself, if I thought they were nice people, but I'd say 'oh,
 I don't like them! They're rough'. But nobody taught me, it just ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were you ever told to curtsey or show respect in someway to anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I don't remember that, no, I don't know whether teachers might have told me but not in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Who d
id the shopkeepers associate with? You said they all dressed up in their frock coats on a Sunday; would they have mixed with each other socially or would they associate with teachers and other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I don't remember. I remember this little cr
owd of men, but I don't know whether they ... 'Course, there was always ... there were teachers and that used to run the ... the boy scouts started. They would run the boy scouts and that sort of thing. Of course, there was no girl guides in those days, B
aden Powell wouldn't have anything to do with women. 'Course, that came along after the South African War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Who would teachers mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, the teachers mostly worked in the local schools. Nearly all teachers lived within walking distance, and 
they ... and we used to have 2 hours for midday which, of course gave them plenty of time to come home. And we used to go to school from 9 'till 12, and then we used to go back to school from 2 'till half past 4. But that 2 hours in the midday was a good 
break.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So teachers lived near their work and they could get home every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, most of them did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Would the teachers have associated with the shopkeepers, for instance, in your area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I don't remember. I don't remember them associating. Of course, they could've done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What sort of people would you say went to the church, and what went to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, of course, there was trades}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5856267\charrsid9898441 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 people went to chapel and to church, I mean, there was a different ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Would you have said any more went to one church than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I think there was more went to the Church of England than to the non-conformist church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living, or would you say
 that there were different groups even within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, I don't know. I really didn't ... You see in those days, you know, it was wrong for a woman to go to work, if any girls ... it was all 'her mother goes to work' (whispered). It wasn't done. And people didn't have lodgers: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5856267\charrsid9898441 'here, they have lodgers' (whis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
pered), see, it was all ... it was a disgrace for a mother to go to work and it was a disgrace to take in lodgers. But if people did do anything like that it was ... you might say th
ere was snobbery amongst all classes, it didn't matter ... You see what I mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, I do. Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I think my father did, you see, because being in the builders' me
rchant business he appreciated not for a man ... what he did for a living, his principles were more important to him than what he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Because he worked with so many different people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I don't think she bothered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you think she saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You mean move from houses ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No; from one sort of social class into another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, I suppose people did it, but I suppose ... say that the neighbourhood they went in thought they were superior and these people thought that the newcomers were not of their standard, they wouldn't ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Wouldn't have anything to do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No. In fact, I think it was more so than what it is today, because today I think people are pretty reasonable, don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, and tolerant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Tolerant, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So you think it was worse then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, definitely. I think the wars, you know, cut that out. You see, everybody had to muck in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you remember anyone being described as a 'real gentleman' or a 'real lady'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, some people ... yes 'oh, she's very nice, 'you know, 'she's a lady'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you know why this was? Why would someone be 'very nice' or 'a lady'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I think it was their general personality. Of course, some people are very rude, aren't they? As I say, they have no tact at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Oh, yes, the policemen always walked by at a certain time. I think that's the best kind of police force we ever had, because today they go round in motorcars and they don't know what's going on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What did you think of him? I mean, what did people think of policemen? Were you scared of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Oh, no, no, we wasn't scared of policemen. I know they used to say, 'I'll tell a policeman', and all that but I was never frightened of policemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, the people were not so wicked in those days, I think he had a lazy life, if you ask me anything (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 It belonged to the firm where my father was employed, you see. That's how it was we used to collect the rents round there
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No. Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You mentioned that they wouldn't have anything to do with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 They might not speak to them but they wouldn't. ... they'd ... kind of keep them aloft, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Have you ever heard the term 'rough music'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 In some areas people were made to leave the area by 'rough music'. For example, a crowd would come and bang saucepans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I never remember anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What age did you first go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I think I was 5.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you go 'till 4.30 even at that age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I went to the private school. We came out about 4 in the private school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 The private school, was that for just girls, or girls and boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Girls and boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How long did you go there for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 'Till I was about 9.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was that a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How did you get on at school, did you like it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I was supposed to be one of the brightest. (laughter) I don't know whether I was, I'm sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, I was very ... I was one of those children that if I couldn't do a thing it worried me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I wasn't keen on the teachers. I think they looked upon the children as something inferior. That was my impression.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Even at the private school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
The private school was better, but the Board school, I thought the teachers had that air of ... you know, they were the only ones who had brains.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 But they weren't like this at the private school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Let's think about the private school first. Did your parents have to pay for you to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes. It was about 6d. a week, I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life? Manners, and tidiness and punctuality? Ways of speaking, etc.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I suppose they did. But of course, the children in those days I think most of them came from nice people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Would they all come from a similar sort of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, yes. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 If there was something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, they'd probably send a note home to your mother. Write a note for you to give to your mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, my father did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, and if you didn't get on very well he told you off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did they visit the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No. They were not interfering people, unless they were asked to go they wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I don't think I knew. I probably wouldn't have the sense to know at that age.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You were happy at your private school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Why did you go to a Board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, you see, these private schools seemed to close down, as these schools ... they just closed down, there was nowhere else to go, without going a long way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So then you went to a Board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, in the same road as where I lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What did you think of that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, to tell you the truth I was all in a muddle when I went to that school. Some of the things they taught I was advanced and the other things I didn't know anything at all. It took me about a year to get in. I appro
ve of these schools today. I think that there's a general education and if a child goes from one to the other it's not all haywire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 But you had this problem when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You had to sort yourself out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, afterwards, which was a nuisance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What did you feel about the teachers then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
I didn't think much of them, I thought they were too busy and talked to the children ... You know, they talked to every child as if it was rough stuff, you know what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were some of them children from ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Some of them were a bit ... I mean, some of them, like, their parents had stalls in market places and they used to go round ... Well, to me it seemed, you know ... They didn't mind how the teacher talked to the
m they were used to being told off, but I wasn't. And I never said anything but I used to think a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did these teachers pick some children out for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I think they had their pets, you know, and that one was alw
ays brought out as being special. And of course, I will say this: you can have a few children in a class and you can't do anything with them and then the teacher gets frustrated and all the children have to suffer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 And this is what happened in your class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, in different classes I've been in, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 If the children did something the teachers disapproved of in this school what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What? The Board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, they'd go out ... they'd be reported to the headmistress and she might give them a hander, and put their name in the punish book.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 It was all girls where I was. Well, it was infants, girls, and then boys on the top floor, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were there any cliques or groups in the Board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, I don't know 'cos we all ... There's something about children, they always know their own class, and the rough ones get together and the quiet ones get together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So this did happen quite naturally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 It did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, I don't remember. I don't remember them being kind of left out. In fact, I think there was more of the thing that 'well, why didn't you come to so-and-so?'
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I went to the Technical School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How old were you when you went to the technical school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I think I was 12 and I left when I was about 16.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I see, was this usual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I was one of the superior ones (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Why was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, there was just ... there was one or two of my friends, we just went there. Of course, in Leyton there was the Technical School in Leyton and there was a technical school in Walthamstow and they were the only two higher ... you know. And
 of course, you couldn't get in there unless you was a certain standard, you always had to have an exam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your teachers encourage you to go there, or did your parents apply for you to go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, as a matter of fact there was a friend of 
mine wanted to go and she wanted someone to go with and she worried me so, and I told my mother. And my brother had been to this school as well. And I said 'Hilda keeps on worrying me, I don't really mind', so she says, 'oh, well, it won't do you any harm
, 'she said, 'you'd better go in for the exam and see if you're good enough'. And that was how it was I went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you enjoy that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, it was very superior, you know, and I think the education was far stiffer than what it is today. I met so
me young women that went in for teaching and that sort of thing and I said 'don't you think we used to do very advanced work?' She said, 'I think Mr. Hills was 10 years advanced' she said. I said 'you know, I used to stop up 'till 12 o'clock at night tryi
ng to get my homework done'.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What subjects did you do, everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Everything. You see, we used to have a different teacher for each subject and each teacher - you'd have 4 subjects of a night. I think it was 4 or 3, yes - and one'd give you ...
 see, you'd probably have maths and English and perhaps some poetry to learn one night. And another night you might have art and ... I don't know whether we had maths every night, we might've done, and then perhaps something else to do, probably some need
le-work or something like that, you see. There was generally 3 subjects of a night and I can remember all Saturday working on homework. And I wasn't the only one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So you were worked hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 And you left there when you were 16?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Would you have stayed longer if you could or was that the ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I was weary. I was worn out. I could have stayed on, by parents would have let me stop on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No. No, I didn't go in for any more evening classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 While you were at school did you have a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I don't know. When was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you get a job immediately you left the technical college?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I stopped at home for a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, about a year. And then I felt I wanted a change and my mother said 'Well, what do you want to do? So I said I 
wouldn't mind being a milliner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Why did you stop at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, I don't know, I was ... You see, everybody was at work, I was the only one at home, and I suppose my father could afford to keep me and they never bothered. It just happened, you se
e. And I know I went to a local shop to make hats and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How did you get this job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 It was an apprenticeship. I don't know, I think I only got about 18 pence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, I used to put linings in hats and I suppose make cups of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, we worked a long time. I think it was 9 in the morning and I think the shop shut at 7 in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you stay there 'till 7?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, well, it was only a local shop, 
I wasn't far away. Of course, we had a lunch hour and a tea hour, a tea break, but it wasn't hard work, I mean, we all used to sit and talk and chat and dew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You sound as if you enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Oh, Miss Philpotts, she was a very important person. She had a very successful business, she was ... you know, a bit superior type, we were only the girls in the workroom. But anyway, I think my mother thought it made some interest in life for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you like or dislike the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, I liked it. I wouldn't have gone if I hadn't liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How long did you stay there for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, I was there I suppose about a year. And what happened? I'll tell you what made a change in my life. I remember 
when King Edward VII died everybody went in mourning and my brother was a tailor's cutter and they were inundated with orders and they asked him if he knew anybody who could do some sewing or help, so he said 'I've got a sister that can sew'. They said, '
Oh, well, fetch her up', and I went up and I stayed there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 When was this, how old were you then? How long were you at the milliner's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I was about 18. And that's where I spent ... I just stayed there. And then, of course, when I was 22 the First W
orld War broke out and then I think everything went to pieces. I mean all the men ... And, of course, my brother ... the war broke out in the August and my brother died the following May.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you stay at this tailor's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you work the same sort of hours there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, it was pretty long hours, but I don't know, we didn't seem to mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, we used to get a fortnight's holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I suppose the money worked out about 18 shillings, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12746567 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 1 a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 It was in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, I used to give Mother about 5 shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How did you get on with the other people you worked with there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, all right. Never had any bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, very nice, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What happened after the War started, did you still stay at this place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, you see, me fath
er died, me brother died, and then I of course stayed at this place because, you see, everything kind of started to close down there wasn't much about. And then I thought to meself, well I'll have to earn some money, I haven't got any father now, you know
,
 and there was a job going in Wood Street in the City. It was a ... in the giving-out department of materials and it was a ladies place. It was a warehouse and they used to make clothes and they used to give material out to people in the East End of Londo
n
, mostly Jews, and they wanted someone to do the booking and checking of the work. And so I wrote after this job and I had an interview and I got the job. And I stayed there. And, oh, then I got married. I got married while I was there, and I stayed there
 'till the end of the War. Well, then fellow I took the job with, he came back and, of course, I was home then, but then me own husband was home then, and I was at home, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Your mother didn't go to work again, not even after your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no, she never went to work. You see, then my mother died. She was only 58 when she died in 1917.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, so that was 3 within ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Three years, fourteen, fifteen ... See, when the War started there was the family of us, there was Dad and my M
um and my brother and I and they all ... at the end of the War I was all alone, you see. Thank goodness I was married, but my husband was out in Gibraltar. But just one of those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What jobs have you done since the First World War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I 
didn't do any work 'till ... when? Of course, my husband came home in 1919 and then my baby was born in 1922, and I don't think I did any work. I don't remember doing any work 'till the Second World War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What did you do then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I was an insurance
 agent. I had an insurance agent come to the door, and ... of course, me daughter, she went into the Services when she was 21, and of course, my husband ... he had a business that was closed down, he got a job. And I was ... there was nothing ... you know
,
 everything was blackouts and one thing and another and this agent came to the door one day, this insurance agent - Royal London - and I said I wish I could get a job 'cos I was just that age of 50 when I wasn't obliged to do work. So he says, 'Look, how 
w
ould you like to have one of these books?' So I said I wouldn't mind. So he says, 'come up to our office' he says. And they showed me the book and what I had to do and I had a wonderful ... well, talk about mixing with people! I went from Hoxton in Shored
itch, and Chingford and Ilford. I think I went all round London. I learnt my way round London, and I did this book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How long did you do that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 About 3 or 4 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 And did you do any other jobs after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I came home and I didn'
t do any more. I didn't do any. My daughter came home and I didn't ... In fact, my husband and my daughter thought it was wrong. I could've kept on with the insurance company but no, they didn't think it was right, and they'd got that printed in them. Mum
s didn't go to work. Isn't funny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Things have changed, haven't they. Would you have preferred another type of occupation, looking back on your working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I don't think so. I don't regret it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no! Nothing so common!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was it thought of as common to belong to trade unions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, you know, yes. You know, unions! (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I suppose there was, but I didn't take much notice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Would you say that full time work changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 After you left school and were working - this is in the earlier part, again - did starting full
 time work change your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No. Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I used to do things on a Sunday. If I wanted to do any needlework, if I wanted to make anything or do anything I used to do
 it. I couldn't be bothered with just sitting and being a good girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did they mind that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, I think they found that I was better occupied than otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you vote at all after the ... yes, you were old enough, weren't you? 1918 I think it started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Yes, that was when the women ... Oh, by the way, I had a friend who was a suffragette and she did open my eyes to the poor deal that women were getting and I began to think in her direction although I never had any activities, but she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 She opened your eyes a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Yes. For one example she gave me, of a woman being left, her husband was a farmer and he died or was killed or something, and she was left with this
 farm to manage, and she had in those days a good many labourers, farm labourers. All those men had a vote. Because she was a woman, she was the woman that was paying them and working them and keeping them in jobs, because she was a woman she hadn't got a
 vote. And it made me begin to think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you then begin to take more of an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, I did, I began to be more sympathetic towards the suffragette movement. At first, of course, the things they used to do, people did feel a bit
 annoyed with them. But as she explained, she said even the men never got anything without making themselves objectionable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Were you able to vote in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was it 1918 they gave the vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I suppose I did vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Can you remember what party you voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I expect it would have been the Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Do you know why you held your views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, as I say, my father was a strong Conservative and I suppose ... as he used to point out, trade was always bett
er and this sort of thing, that I suppose I thought it was better for the community. Because if there's plenty of work about it's a good sign. And of course, in those days there were plenty of unemployment. The working man in the wintertime, he was very h
ard hit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way or did you do different things when you started working? Did you go out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No. No, I was really a home bird.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You'd do your sewing and things at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 That's it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you make any new friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, I had a very nice friend that I met. She was very nice, but I didn't make a lot of friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you bring any home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 The year when you weren't working at all what did you do with yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I used to help me mother. I think she used to make jolly good use of me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you enjoy being at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes. I think that my generation, we were more for the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You said earlier on that your father liked to k
now where you were going, is this the time when you meant? When you started working, that he liked to know where you were going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, after I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, I always had to be in by 10!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 And he told you off if you came in later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What age were you when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 I was 24.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How long had you known your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, about 4 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, he was friendly with a young woman that
 I was working with. And she used to cycle to work, and he used to cycle to his place. And one day she hadn't got her bicycle, she was ... we were walking along to the buses and he came along on his bike and he stopped and we talked, and it appeared he li
ved in Leyton as well as me. Well, of course, after that I used to see him occasionally and one Saturday he saw me and he says to me, 'are you doing anything tomorrow?' So I said, 'no, why? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6566024\charrsid9898441 W}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 hat's the matter?' So he said, 'my two pals have fixed themselves up with girls and I'm all on me own'. (laughter) And that was the beginning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 And he came from Leyton, did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, he lived in Vicarage Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So did you start going out with him after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, yes, and that was the beginning of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How lovely! Did you save up money before getting married, or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, I was always a saver. I was brought up to save, if it was only a penny, I'd got to save it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did your parents help you in setting up a home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, no, not really 'cos Father had died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, about 2 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Could you describe the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, it was very quiet, very quiet. Just my husband's mother and my mother and ... You see, the War was on. We were just married and th
at was that, there wasn't any feast or ... well, you couldn't get the stuff. And of course, he was going in the Navy. You see, he was going in the Navy. I think that was one reason why we were married, you see, he said 'well, I've know you a long time and
 if I get killed you will be me widow and you will get an allowance,' he said, 'I can't see the time ... wasting all these years ... 'and that was how it was we were married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, no! No honeymoon, and besides there was n
owhere to have a honeymoon. I mean, all the coast was blockaded in some way, 'cos of course, the submarines were terrible in those days. I think it was ... was it 1917? I think we were worse off than people realised. I can remember being up in London and 
there was a fish shop only had a few herrings in the shop on Christmas Eve. We were very, very short. Very short.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did you get married in church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 No, my husband, ... he was peculiar about that. We were married in a registry office. He said that ..
. he had funny ideas. He said that with all this wickedness going on he thought it was ridiculous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 A lot of people share those views.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes. He said, 'after all, 'he said,' marriage is only a man-made law. 'He was right, I mean, it's only ... prot
ect women ... I mean, some people have no principles at all, if it wasn't for certain laws it'd be terrible what would happen. Men'd go off and leave women with children, wouldn't they? And no principles at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Where did you live after you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, in 1918 I lived with my mother-in-law in Vicarage Road, and then in 1918 I moved to Hoe Street, Walthamstow and that's where my daughter was born, in Hoe Street. Now we live in Hoe Lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 It was 1918 when you moved to Hoe Street, Walthamstow, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, that was ... Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How old was your husband when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 He was 29.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What was your husband's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, he worked as a ... he was a clerk in a piano ... Murdock's. I don't know whether you've heard of Mutdock's.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
He was there. And then when he came home after the War he said he wasn't going to work there any more. They wanted to pay them the wages what they left at, so he had ... It's a funny thing, his father had a builders' merchants
 years ago, and his uncle, they were in that line of business. In fact, if you go along the Lea Bridge Road you'll see our name up near the railway station ... Lea Bridge Road, there's C. Barralet }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12746567 &}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441  Co, yes. And he went in with his uncle, and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 To help with the builders' merchants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What did he actually do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Well, he kind of managed things and he ... He was, he was a good manager and he seemed to ... Of course, his grandfather had had a business in the Gray}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12388339\charrsid9898441 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 s Inn R
oad, builders' merchants, and although he really did the clerical work and all that sort of thing, he seemed to know exactly what bricks were and flowerpots and everything without ... And I used to say to him ... He used to say 'that's a so-and-so firebri
ck', or something. And I said, 'who told you?' He said, 'nobody'. It was born in him, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 You say he joined the Navy during the War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, he was called up, you see, there was no building going on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 What did he do in the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 He wor
ked on a motor boat. He went out ... he was in the Mediterranean for two years. He was a coxswain on this motor boat, in the end. And when the German submarines used to be showing a periscope they used to fly along in these little boats and drop a bomb on
 them. And after the War he had a lot of prize money for the boats ... to their record that they kept from ... Because the German submarines were terrible in the First World War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Was he a private in the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Well, he joined as an ordinary sailor
, but as I say ... he never got on a commission or anything like that, but he was a coxswain on the boat, which was like a s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12388339\charrsid9898441 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
rgeant in the ordinary ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 That sounds dangerous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he stay with his uncle's firm all his life or did he have any other job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
He branched off and then we used to make these fireplaces like that. He had his own business and had his own factory and everything which of course ... he took that over on his own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Making fireplaces?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Like that, yes. Of course, they're dying out now, nobody had fireplaces.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 So he eventually had his own business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 
Yes. And then, of course, the Second World War came along, and that went. And then he got a job just ... I think he was clerking, or something in some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16281805\charrsid9898441 am}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 munition place, or something, or some sort of job. You can guess it was something to do with the War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 This was during the War, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Did he work after the War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, yes, he started up again in this sort of thing, but he was take
n ill and he died in 1952. You see, he only lived 7 years after the War. But for a time while he was ill I used to manage his business for him, but of course, when he went I faded right out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8211949 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 How did your husband feel about you working after you first got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9597288 EB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15170580\charrsid9898441 Oh, he never wanted me to go to work. Oh, no. Oh, no. It wasn't done.
\par }}